item.name: Likewise Service Manager – (lwsmd)
item.description: enables joining the host to a Microsoft Active Directory domain and then authentication of users through AD.

item.name: VMware Platform Services Controller Health Monitor - (pschealthd)
item.description: Monitors the health and status of all core Platform Services Controller infrastructure services.

item.name: VMware HTTP Reverse Proxy - (rhttpproxy)
item.description: The reverse proxy runs on each Platform Services Controller node and each vCenter Server system. It is a single entry point into the node and enables services that run on the node to communicate securely.

item.name: VMware Appliance Monitoring Service - (statsMonitor)
item.description: Monitor the vCenter Server Appliance guest operating system resource consumption.

item.name: VMware Appliance Management Service – (applmgmt)
item.description: appliance configuration and provides public API endpoints for appliance lifecycle management. Included on the Platform Services Controller appliance.

item.name: VMware Authentication Framework - (vmafdd)
item.description: Service that provides a client-side framework for vmdir authentication and serves the VMware Endpoint Certificate Store (VECS).

item.name: VMware Ceritficate Service - (vmcad)
item.description:
Provisions each VMware software component that has the vmafd client libraries and each ESXi host with a signed certificate that has VMCA as the root certificate authority. You can change the default certificates by using the Certificate Manager utility.
VMware Certificate Service uses the VMware Endpoint Certificate Store (VECS) to serve as a local repository for certificates on every Platform Services Controller instance. Although you can decide not to use VMCA and instead can use custom certificates, you must add the certificates to VECS.

item.name: VMware DIrectory Service - (vmdird)
item.description:
Provides a multitenant, multimastered LDAP directory service that stores authentication, certificate, lookup, and license information. Do not update data in vmdird by using an LDAP browser.
If your domain contains more than one Platform Services Controller instance, an update of vmdir content in one vmdir instance is propagated to all other instances of vmdir.

item.name: VMware Service Lifecycle Manager - (vmon)
item.description: Start and stop vCenter Server services and monitor service API health. The vmware-vmon service is a centralized platform-independent service that manages the lifecycle of Platform Services Controller and vCenter Server. Exposes APIs and CLIs to third-party applications.

item.name: VMware License Service – (vmware-cis-license)
item.description: Each PSC includes VMware License Service, which manages and delivers centralized licenses and has a reporting functionality to VMware products in your environment. The license service inventory replicates across all Platform Services Controller in the domain at 30-second intervals.

item.name: VMware Component Manager Service - (vmware-cm)
item.description: is included in the Platform Services Controller Services and is responsible for service registration and lookup functionalities in the group. If the Component Manager Service Health Alarm fires, check whether the Component Manager Service is running. In case the service is stopped, try starting it again. For more information on stopping, starting and restarting vCenter Server 6.x services

item.name: VMware Service Control Agent - (vmware-sca)
item.description: Manages service configurations. You can use the service-control CLI to manage individual service configurations.

item.name: VMware Identity Management Service - (vmware-sts)
item.description: Services behind the vCenter Single Sign-On feature, which provide secure authentication services to VMware software components and users.

item.name: VMware Security Token Service - (vmware-stsd)
item.description: By using vCenter Single Sign-On, the VMware components communicate using a secure SAML token exchange mechanism. vCenter Single Sign-On constructs an internal security domain (vsphere.local by default) where the VMware software components are registered during installation or upgrade.

item.name: VMware vAPI Endpoint
item.description: The vSphere Automation API endpoint provides a single point of access to vAPI services. You can change the properties of the vAPI Endpoint service from the vSphere Client. See the vSphere Automation SDKs Programming Guide for details on vAPI endpoints.

item.name: Vcenter Server Service Daemon - (vpxd)
item.description: If this service is stopped then we will not able to connect to Vcenter Server via Vsphere client.
